
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">If you’ve not used this service before</h2>

<p>You can use this service to apply for a guarantee on bonds, loans and other bank facilities that support UK exporters.</p>

<p>Only approved staff at these banks can use this service currently:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Barclays Bank</li>
  <li>HSBC</li>
  <li>Lloyds Bank</li>
  <li>Bank of Scotland</li>
  <li>Westminster Bank</li>
  <li>Royal Bank of Scotland</li>
  <li>Ulster Bank</li>
  <li>Santander UK</li>
</ul>

<p>Guarantees are provided by UK Export Finance under the terms of the master guarantee agreement (MGA) for either the:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Bond Support Scheme</li>
  <li>General Export Facility Scheme</li>
</ul>

<p>Your bank must comply with the terms of the MGA you’re applying for.  The MGA is signed between your bank and UK Export Finance.</p>
